The paper discusses the limitations of existing Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs) and proposes new architectures that make use of multi-scale information and deep structures. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on deep learning architectures and their applications to graph-structured problems, we believe that cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV.
